modules.description: This module trains and evaluates Random Forest models for regression or classification tasks using the ranger C++ library. It operates on CSV data files and supports parallel execution for both training and prediction, with explicit control over tree count and feature selection during splitting. The trained model is saved to disk, and predictions return both estimated values and their standard deviations.

This module calculates standard deviation of float lists, enforces runtime conditions with descriptive errors, manipulates tuples by prepending elements or extracting fields, combines three lists into a list of triples, and executes functions with a temporary file path. It works with lists, tuples of various lengths, and file operations. Concrete uses include data validation, statistical analysis, and temporary file handling during computations.

This module contains two submodules: one for training and evaluating Random Forest models from CSV data with parallel execution, and another for statistical calculations, tuple manipulation, and temporary file handling. It works with lists, tuples, CSV files, and machine learning models. Concrete uses include regression and classification tasks, data validation, and statistical analysis with standard deviation.
